                            <comment id="12502003" author="james.kennedy" created="Wed, 6 Jun 2007 17:40:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The above batch update description implies batch update of columns for a single row.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another possibility is batch update of multiple rows wherein the client buffers up a number of row updates and flushes them out together.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12511500" author="jimk" created="Tue, 10 Jul 2007 17:26:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Another possibility is batch update of multiple rows wherein the client buffers up a number&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; of row updates and flushes them out together.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may still require multiple RPCs if the rows being updated are in different regions and are being served by different servers. However, the client could split the batch into per-server chunks, which would still greatly reduce the number of RPCs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12512877" author="jimk" created="Mon, 16 Jul 2007 07:05:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Works in my environment. Ensure Hudson agrees.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12513060" author="hadoopqa" created="Mon, 16 Jul 2007 22:00:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12361870/patch.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12361870/patch.txt&lt;/a&gt; applied and successfully tested against trunk revision r556707.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test results:   &lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.zones.apache.org:8080/hudson/job/Hadoop-Patch/419/testReport/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lucene.zones.apache.org:8080/hudson/job/Hadoop-Patch/419/testReport/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Console output: &lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.zones.apache.org:8080/hudson/job/Hadoop-Patch/419/console&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lucene.zones.apache.org:8080/hudson/job/Hadoop-Patch/419/console&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12513076" author="jimk" created="Mon, 16 Jul 2007 22:20:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12515352" author="jimk" created="Wed, 25 Jul 2007 17:17:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Michael Stack and I were discussing the current implementation and there are multiple problems with updating more than a single row at a time:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a region might be reassigned between the start of the batch update and the commit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a region split might occur&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the server might receive a shut down request before all the commits complete&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if a lot of data is being passed, the rpc could time out before all the data is transmitted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;We came up with this list in a short five minute discussion and I&apos;m sure we could think of a lot more issues without trying too hard.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For these reasons we decided that batch updates should be limited to a single row and consequently this issue is being reopened.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12515864" author="jimk" created="Thu, 26 Jul 2007 21:02:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Restricts batches to one row per batch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12515865" author="jimk" created="Thu, 26 Jul 2007 21:03:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Works in my environment. Try to get the +1 from Hudson.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
